Plug-in name: Sparecode
Plug-in shortname: sparecode
Description: code cleaner

Most options of the form '-sparecode-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-sparecode-no-option-name'.

Most options of the form '-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-no-option-name'.

Options taking a string as argument should preferably be written
-option-name="argument".

***** LIST OF AVAILABLE OPTIONS:

-sparecode          perform a spare code analysis (opposite option is
                    -no-sparecode)
-sparecode-analysis  alias for option -sparecode
-sparecode-annot    select more things to keep every reachable annotation
                    (set by default, opposite option is -sparecode-no-annot)
-sparecode-rm-unused-globals  only remove unused global types and variables
                    (automatically done by -sparecode-analysis) (opposite
                    option is -sparecode-no-rm-unused-globals)

*** DEBUG

-sparecode-debug <n>  level of debug for plug-in Sparecode (default to 0)

*** GETTING INFORMATION

-sparecode-help     help of plug-in Sparecode
-sparecode-h        alias for option -sparecode-help

*** OUTPUT MESSAGES

-sparecode-log <K_1:file_1,...>  copy log messages from Sparecode to a file.
                    <K> is a combination of these characters:
                    a: ALL messages (equivalent to 'dfiruw')
                    d: debug       e: user or internal error (same as 'iu')
                    f: feedback    i: internal error
                    r: result      u: user error    w: warning
                    An empty <K> (e.g. ":file.txt") defaults to 'iruw'. One
                    plug-in can output to several files and vice-versa.
                    (preferably use -sparecode-log="K_1:file_1,...")
-sparecode-msg-key <k1[,...,kn]>  enables message display for categories
                    <k1>,...,<kn>. Use -sparecode-msg-key help to get a list
                    of available categories, and * to enable all categories
                    (preferably use -sparecode-msg-key="k1[,...,kn]")
-sparecode-verbose <n>  level of verbosity for plug-in Sparecode (default to
                    1)
-sparecode-warn-key <k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]>  set warning status for category
                    <k1> to <s1>,...,<kn> to <sn>. Use -sparecode-warn-key
                    help to get a list of available categories, and * to
                    enable all categories. Possible statuses are inactive,
                    feedback, warning, error, abort, feedback-once,
                    warning-once, error-once. Defaults to warning.
                    (preferably use
                    -sparecode-warn-key="k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]")
